<title>USA: Ceridian acquires software developer.</title>
<headline>Ceridian acquires software developer.</headline>
<dateline>MINNEAPOLIS 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ceridian Corp said Friday it has acquired Innovative Business and Training Solutions Inc, a software developer that performs corporate human resources functions, for an undisclosed amount.</p>
<p>Innovative Solutions is based in Cuyahoga Falls, Ohio, and had revenue of nearly $2 million in 1996, Ceridian said. Its products provide self-service applications allowing workers and managers to handle tasks such as enrolling for benefits, exploring job postings, planning career options and examining online policy manuals.</p>
<p>--((Reuter Chicago Newsdesk 312-408-8787))</p>
